{"TopicId":149576,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Why isn\u0026#039;t my mun periapsis showing on encounter?","CreatedByName":"BrandonM","CreatedById":169978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T01:51:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"BrandonM","CreatedById":169978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T01:51:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI need help with this, fairly new, so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=778309418\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=778309418\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-10T01:51:45Z\u0022 title=\u002210/10/2016 01:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by BrandonM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Stargate525","CreatedById":53585,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T01:58:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s because when you cross over into the Mun\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E, you\u0027ll find you\u0027re on a collision course with it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BrandonM","CreatedById":169978,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T02:16:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222795232\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476064699\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002253585\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stargate525\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Stargate525 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s because when you cross over into the Mun\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E, you\u0027ll find you\u0027re on a collision course with it. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow does one exit the collision course?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T02:22:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222795247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476065819\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BrandonM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, BrandonM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow does one exit the collision course?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne could burn. In pretty \u00A0much any direction that is not directly pointed at the Mun, although those directions that are in the plane that is perpendicular to\u00A0the collision course have a reputation of being particularly effective.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plusck","CreatedById":153264,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T04:02:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222795247\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022149576\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476065819\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022169978\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BrandonM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, BrandonM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow does one exit the collision course?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA very small burn, somewhere between radial-out and retrograde, should set you on a perfect low-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Periapsis\u0022\u003EPe\u003C/abbr\u003E encounter. Radial-out will make you encounter the Mun earlier (therefore before you reach such a high altitude); retrograde will make you encounter the Mun at a lower altitude (but will slow you down and make the encounter later). Between the two should therefore be perfect...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Reactordrone","CreatedById":110060,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-10T06:31:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClicking on the target planet and selecting focus view will show you the orbit line as it will appear when you\u0027re within the sphere of influence of that body. It can help you to fine tune your orbit in cases like this. a small prograde or retrograde burn should fix that up easily.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}